-- Bankers Confidence Index Drops to 64%, Mortgage Index Declines, PBOC Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-17T09:18:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/bankers-confidence-index-drops-to-64-mortgage-index-declines-pboc-says.html

          
          
             The confidence index of Chinese
bankers fell 5.8 percentage points in the second quarter from
the previous quarter to 64 percent, the People’s Bank of China
said today.  
 Of the 2,900 heads of financial institutions tracked in the
survey, 57.9 percent said monetary policies were
“appropriate,” 2.6 percentage points lower than the previous
quarter, the central bank said on its website.  
 The index of loan demand dropped to 66.9 percent in the
second quarter from the previous quarter, with the gauge of
mortgage lending falling by 6.4 percentage points to 58.8
percent, according to the central bank’s survey.  
